rComments: Jeff Parker is funny, intelligent, passionate, and interesting. Makes you want to go to his classes and really use your brain. Lectures are laid-back but engaging. As a prof he is creative, kind and helpful. Just tough enough in marking to let you know he actually pays attention to the merit of your ideas. Would take his classes again.
had him for american lit! he's really funny and personable. Picked really good books. overall, great course and great lecturer. he likes to get to know his students
